The paper deals with computational and structural properties of Boolean satisfiability problems, which are central to computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses graph-theoretic properties of the solution space, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of heuristics and algorithms in the paper suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper establishes dichotomies in Schaefer's framework, which is a logical framework, suggesting that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
